				<p>@Martin; I wasn&#8217;t aware that CSS3 Pie supported transform, but that could be I&#8217;ve been too focused on my own <a href="http://www.useragentman.com/blog/csssandpaper-a-css3-javascript-library/" rel="nofollow">cssSandpaper</a> script, which has for a while (in fact, it is what the Transforms Translator uses to do the transformation and generate the matrix code).  While both of these solutions are great for supporting CSS3 transforms, both solutions require JavaScript, which some developers may want to use in all situations (e.g. to cut down on download time).  This gives a viable alternative.  It also explains how IE works and will give developers a way to explore how IE&#8217;s Visual Filters technology works, since they work quite differently than their CSS3 equivalents.</p>
 
								
